      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presenting an impeccable 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S (996.2), finished in Arctic Silver over black supple leather. This example features the robust 3.6L flat-six M96 powerplant, delivering 320 hp through a precise 6-speed longitudinal manual gearbox and an all-wheel-drive system with a viscous map-controlled clutch. The mechanical integrity is superlative; the IMS bearing has been proactively addressed with a dual-row ceramic retrofit, and the rear main seal remains bone dry. This C4S utilizes the Turbo-derived widebody chassis and braking system, including four-piston monobloc calipers and ventilated cross-drilled rotors. The suspension geometry is factory-spec with Bilstein dampers providing optimal damping rates. Zero evidence of bore scoring or electrolytic corrosion. A true collector-grade specimen with a fully documented service history and a flawless DME overrev report.",
